le - granted I did not camp it, I bought it. Personally I think the T-staff is overrated. Perhaps it harkens to the day when great DPS weapons were rare - when Kunark was released even the Fighting Baton was considered amazing. With a dex over 200 it did not proc enough for me to think it was much better than my Sceptre of Mastery and Staff of Shielding combo. (Without the proc it is an over priced Peacebringer.) The ten weight does not help its cause, nor does the fact that the stun rarely actually holds for more than a few seconds. The DD and the DPS is very nice, but is it worth 30k? Only you can decide. <br><br>**Disclaimer**<br>Solely the Opinion of this 52nd Solo Monk (W/Fungi)<br><br>-Kixim- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujorlenrizzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jorlen Rizzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 9:44:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11675.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> tstaff</span><hr size=1> I remember when I first saved up enough to get myself one of these.  I am now level 56, and I still have and use one.  I've tried about just about every purchaseable weapon, including high end 1handers, but have not found any that can compare to the usefulness and DPS output of this fine weapon.<br><br>The weight?  I could care less.  Yeah I loose 20ish ac.  Big deal.  It's worth it.  The proc owns, it fires off 3-4 times a fight sometimes and my dex is only 130ish.  The proc has turned the table on a fight for me many a times, stunning and nuking a mob that would have usually killed me.  I agree that procs should not be counted on.. but can you name me a weapon that procs 120dd full damage everytime, with a stun that can't be resisted?  Even if it lasts .1 seconds, you just stopped that caster from completing his spell.  It's hard to beat the 100 blows effect as a proc.<br><br>You have 30k?  I say play the market and get the rest, or keep saving up for one, you aren't very far from it now.  I got mine for 45k after I had initially sold it when I started my SK.  That <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> was last week</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, I'm on Drinal as well, so if you keep an eye open on the market you can find it for cheap.  <br><br>I'm sure that person would have taken 40k but I didn't want to push my luck.  As far as if it's over-rated and such, that's only for you to decide..  I &lt;3 my tstaff, no weapon can compare.  In any case, best of luck man.  If you ever need advice or PC on anything, send Jorlen a tell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelfusab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elfus AB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 9:52:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11675.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: T-staff</span><hr size=1> Proc it on a mob thats  about to quad you for 400s. <br><br>Tank a lvl60 mob with a Peace Bringer, than try again with your SoM and SoS and than once again with TStaff. Cleric probably be close to oom on Peace Bringer , you probably be dead trying it with your SoM and SoS (reposte will kill you I say!) and if you did it with the TStaff, you'd probably think lvl60 mobs are too easy and your cleric probably only had to heal you 3 times (slowed of course).<br><br>TStaff harkens to no days of early Kunark where you had no other weapon to really compare. TStaff in my hands has never had its proc resisted, ever. I fight Lodi, guardianwurms, reavers, cliff golems and whatever 100% resist mobs with it all the time and when that stun procs, those mobs don't hit. And when they hit in huge chunks of damage, stunning them even for a second is a huge mana saver for your healer. <br><br>Ther are somethings in EQ a monk should push hard to get and once gotten, never let go....epic, Fungi and TSTaff. Ther are better DPS weapons in 1hb H2H or 2hb, but none has a damn near unresistable stun proc that goes off as much. Ther are many situations where this proc is of unbelievable use and I have used it in many of these situations to help repay the cost of my TStaff at least 100 times over.<br><br>However you have to get it, push yourself to get a TStaff. Of course this does not include ninjaing it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uraign.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raign</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 10:21:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11675.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.exoduszek.com/uploads/yyangbiglb1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tstaff blues</span><hr size=1> What Elfus said.<br><br>It seems useful when it prevents a mob that hits you 2X for 100pts of damage from hitting you, it seem GODLY when it prevents a mob that hits you 4X for 300 from hitting you.  Use it at level 60, use dozen or so other weapons that are obtainable without a nTOV guild at level 60 (SoM, SoS, PB, IFS, KK, Epic, WF, ZK, FoI, Skybreaker, Knotted Knuckles), then grin to yourself every time you hear someone say "it's over-rated".<br><br>Skybreaker + SoM MIGHT (to lazy to do the math atm) out damage it, but is nowhere near as useful.. any other combo.. simply does not stack up to the damage or more importantly the usefulness.<br><br>Buy a fungi.. when you have a fungi, buy a tstaff. <p><p><b><font color="#7D020F">_______________________________________________</font></b></p><p> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85329"><i><b><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><font face="Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, san-serif" color="7D020F">Raign   Deranged </font></font></b></i></a><font color="#0000A0"> --</font> <font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" color="#0000A0">Proud   member of <a href="http://www.unyieldingpower.com"><b><i>Unyielding Power</i></b></a></font><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><br>  </font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><i><font size="-1">If you think   that I am NUTS...</font></i></font> <p><font size="-1"><i><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif">you should talk   to this guy in my head!!</font></i></font></p><p><b><font color="#7D020F">_______________________________________________</font></b></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubututsunami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ButuTsunami</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/1/02 5:09:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11675.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eqtoolbox.not.net/images/forum/avatar/121.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tstaff blues</span><hr size=1> The <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>only</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> time the Tstaff has ever let me down was fighting the ogre guards outside of Oggok for giggles with a group that was about to go into Fear